-- Canada's Harper Says Omar Khadr Faces Serious Charges, Declines to Comment
-- B y   A l e x a n d r e   D e s l o n g c h a m p s
-- 2010-10-15T15:52:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-15/canada-s-harper-says-omar-khadr-faces-serious-charges-declines-to-comment.html
Canadian Prime Minister Stephen
Harper said today Omar Khadr faces very serious charges in the
U.S. and that his government will wait for the outcome of his
case before commenting further.  Harper was speaking to reporters in Woodbridge, Ontario.
Khadr is the only Canadian citizen to be held by the U.S. in
Guantanamo Bay, Cuba.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexandre Deslongchamps in Ottawa at 
 adeslongcham@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Badertscher at 
 pbadertscher@bloomberg.net  